quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  40,67,"He is The (One) Who created you of dust, thereafter of a sperm-drop, thereafter of a clot; thereafter He brings you out as a young child, thereafter that you (may) reach full age; (Literally: reach your strongest \"age\") thereafter you (may) be aged. And (some) of you are taken (i.e., die) up earlier, and that you (may) reach a stated term, and that possibly you would consider"
  40,68,"He is The (One) who gives life and makes to die; so when He decrees a Command, then surely He only says to it, \"Be!\" and it is"
  40,69,Have you not regarded the ones who dispute concerning the signs of Allah; however are they turned about
  40,70,"The ones who have cried lies to the Book and that wherewith We sent Our Messengers, will then eventually know"
  40,71,"As the shackles are on their necks, and (also) the chains; they are pulled"
  40,72,Into the scalding water; thereafter they are to be seethed in the Fire
  40,73,"Thereafter it is said to them, \"Where are the ones you used to associate"
  40,74,"Apart from Allah?\" They will say, \"They have erred away from us; no indeed, we used not to invoke anything earlier.\" Thus Allah leads the disbelievers into error"
  40,75,"That is (due to the fact) that you used to exult in the earth untruthfully, (Literally: without the truth) and (due to the fact) that you used to live in merriment"
  40,76,"Enter the gates of Hell, eternally (abiding) therein.\" Miserable then is the lodging of the proud (ones)"
  40,77,"So (endure) patiently; surely the promise of Allah is true. So whether We definitely show you some of (the pains) We promise them or We definitely take you up (to Us), then to Us they will be returned"